Mamelodi residents have given councilors a stern warning – fix our problems now or else. They’ve been given 14-days to respond to and resolve residents’ electricity and service delivery complaints. eNCA's Pule Letshwiti-Jones has more. Courtesy #DStv403 PRETORIA - Mamelodi residents have given councilors a stern warning. The councilors have been given 14-days to respond to and resolve residents’ electricity and service delivery complaints. READ: SA’s electricity crisis | President promises power solutions soon They have also called on Tshwane Mayor Randall Williams to come down and hear some of the demands and challenges they are confronted with on a daily basis. Both sides met on Saturday after residents threatened to embark on a total shutdown.